<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well, nothing clearly defined no.<P>there is a gorup bonus for fighting more than one at a time. this is automatic on linked MOBs, but only occurs on non-linked if you have them aggro you at the same time. Mez or Debuff will not do it because you are triggering the aggro by an outside influence. But sending your pet in then putting them on defensive to bring em back to you will.<P>The camp bonus woudl better be described as an age bonus. This is a bonus that accummulates the longer a MOB lives. Then each respawn will have this elssen untill there is no camp bonus. this can even go negative once a spot is overcamped reducing the base XP for each kill.<P>BAF automatically triggers the group bonus also. But multiple gorups hunting near the same area reduces the camp bonus very quickly. Now sometimes a gorup bonus does not register in parenthesis, just like hwne your camp bonus goes negative you do not see a negative number displayed in the parenthesis.<P>Basically the ONLY items that do register are the inherent bonuses generated by Code based on Age or BAF/Link. Anything else, even if it is there, usually does not have a coded text readout. If you watch the levels of the target and actually track the XP you can see the changes though.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
