<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Camp bonus is what you get when you kill mobs that have not been killed for a while.  This is the bonus that goes down as you stay in one spot.<P>Group bonus is the bonus that is awarded for fighting mobs that are linked or when multiple mobs come as a result of Mythic's "Bring a Friend" coding. This bonus is called group bonus because it is groups that will cause baf to happen. Another thing that happens with linked and bafed mobs is that the last one in the chain of linked or baf'ed that dies will drop a chest that contains extra coin.<P>You can not force the group bonus to happen.  If I am solo and see two arawnites standing to gether and i cast a single target debuff on one and only one comes I will not get group bonus (only one will come unless they are linked.) Now, if the same two mobs are standing near each other and I cast an ae debuff that hits both, both will come, but i will still get no group bonus or chest.<P>The same applies to making aggro with the pet. Same two mobs and I send my pet to attack one and the other agros as well because the pet is close and fighting. Still no group bonus or chest. <P>The ONLY way to get group bonus is to get linked mobs or generate baf by being grouped, period.<P>Battik
</FONT>
